# Security Checklist

## Input Validation

All user input must be validated via DTOs:

```typescript
export class CreateTournamentDto {
  @IsString()
  @MinLength(3)
  @MaxLength(100)
  name: string;

  @IsInt()
  @Min(2)
  @Max(10)
  max_players: number;
}
```

## SQL Injection Prevention

Always use parameterized queries:

```typescript
// Bad: SQL injection risk
await this.repo.query(`SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = '${name}'`);

// Good: parameterized
await this.repo.query(`SELECT * FROM users WHERE name = $1`, [name]);

// Good: TypeORM query builder (auto-parameterized)
await this.repo.findOne({ where: { name } });
```

## Authentication

- Routes require JWT by default (global guard)
- Use `@Public()` decorator only for truly public endpoints
- Never expose user passwords or hashed passwords in responses

```typescript
@Get("profile")
// JWT required (default)
getProfile(@CurrentUser() user: User) {}

@Post("login")
@Public()  // Explicitly public
login(@Body() dto: LoginDto) {}
```

## Rate Limiting

Public endpoints must have rate limiting:

```typescript
@Throttle({ default: { limit: 5, ttl: 60000 } })
@Post("login")
login() {}
```

## Secrets

Never hardcode secrets:

```typescript
// Bad
const secret = "my-jwt-secret";

// Good
const secret = this.config.get("jwtSecret");
```

## Bot Endpoint Validation

Validate bot endpoints before making requests:

```typescript
// The UrlValidatorService checks:
// - Valid URL format
// - Not localhost/private IPs in production
// - HTTPS in production
```

## Sensitive Data in Logs

Never log:
- Passwords or password hashes
- JWT tokens
- Full credit card numbers
- Player hole cards (use masked representation)

```typescript
// Bad
this.logger.log("Login attempt", { password: dto.password });

// Good
this.logger.log("Login attempt", { email: dto.email });
```
